  "prompt": "Operator: GELU activation (out = 0.5 * x * (1 + erf(x / sqrt(2)))); compose asc2.erf, multiplication, and addition. Input shapes: [1, 128], [4, 2048], [32, 4096]. Output shape: same_as_input. Dtype: float16. Layout: contiguous. Axis: null. Tiling: flatten each test shape to 1D (size = product of dims) inside the host launcher; the kernel takes `size: int` and tiles 1D with `asc2.tensor(x_ptr, [size])`, `asc2.load(x_gm, [tile_size], offsets=[tile_offset])`, `asc2.store(out, out_gm, offsets=[tile_offset])` \u2014 all ranks 1. Do NOT use 2D `asc2.tensor(..., [num_rows, num_cols])` with a 1D `[tile_size]` load and 2D `[row_idx, col_idx]` offsets; v2 raises `RuntimeError: rank of 'tensor_shape' must match rank of 'shape'`. Place `asc2.sqrt(0.5)` INSIDE the @asc2.jit body (not at module level \u2014 module-level `asc2.*` raises `AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'create_math_SqrtOp'`). TILE_SIZE=128, CORE_NUM=16; partition tile_per_core via `asc2.range(tile_per_block, unroll_factor=2, parallel=True)`. Tail: aligned_only. Accumulator: null. Tolerance: atol=5e-2, rtol=5e-2 against 0.5 * x * (1 + np.vectorize(math.erf)(x / np.sqrt(2))); host reference uses `import math; _verf = np.vectorize(math.erf)` because np.erf and scipy.special.erf are not in this environment. Platform: Ascend950PR_9599. Build/run: python3.10 kernel.py -r Model -v Ascend950PR_9599. Evidence: kernel.py (skills-on adds design.md + verification.md).",
